Hi Darryl,

>What is the value of 4^2^3?
>
>[Difficulty]
>The problem could be read as 16^3 or 4^8.  Without any grouping 
>symbols which is correct?

The correct grouping would be 

  (4^2)^3

although we've never been able to find an 'authoritative' reference
for this.  The safest thing to do is to always use parentheses to
indicate the grouping you want, instead of relying on convention. 

